Kubernetes Pod networking requirements;

1. Each Pod gets it's own IP.
2. All pods can communicate with other pods without NAT.
3. The IP of the pod is same throughout the cluster.

Pod in one namespace can ping a pod in different namespace by default.


using network policies we can control the traffic flow on IP level or port basis.

[root@control ~]# kubectl get pods -A -o wide
